{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781459286570,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_eEmQA515Qk87ABzjxdCt0127","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Figma MCP Wiring (optional, via Code Mode)\"\n3: description: \"Wiring the OPTIONAL Figma MCP into this project's Code Mode: the already-registered Framelink figma manual, the prefixed .env token, the discover-first flow, and a runnable call_tool_chain example. The CLI works fully alone; the MCP is opt-in.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"figma mcp\"\n6:   - \"figma mcp code mode\"\n7:   - \"figma-developer-mcp\"\n8:   - \"pull figma design context\"\n9:   - \"figma get_design_context\"\n10: importance_tier: \"normal\"\n11: contextType: \"implementation\"\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Figma MCP Wiring (optional, via Code Mode)\n15: \n16: > **IMPORTANT:** This skill works **fully with the `figma-ds-cli` alone** — the MCP is **opt-in**. Before invoking any Figma MCP tool, always **discover first** (`search_tools` / `tool_info`) and confirm the `figma` manual and its exact tool names are present. Never guess a tool name, and never claim the MCP works until discovery confirms it.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Core Principle\n23: \n24: Wiring here means the agent reaches Figma's **read** surface — design context, variables, metadata — through this project's **Code Mode** transport. The Code Mode manual named `figma` is **already registered** in `.utcp_config.json` (community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp`, stdio, `npx`); nothing new needs to be installed for the MCP path. The only setup step is a `.env` entry with a Figma personal access token.\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: \n28: - Pull Figma file/node data into the agent so it can generate or reconcile code against a design.\n29: - The work is codegen-from-design, not authoring or exporting from the live Desktop session.\n30: \n31: The CLI vs MCP routing line:\n32: \n33: - **`figma-ds-cli` (CLI) = author/modify/export IN Figma.** It drives the live Figma Desktop session to create/render/modify nodes, manage tokens and variables, and export assets/JSX/CSS/screenshots. This is the primary surface.\n34: - **Figma MCP (Code Mode) = pull design data INTO the agent for codegen.** Use it only when the agent needs Figma design context as model input (file/node data, variables, screenshots) to generate or align code. The MCP does not drive Figma Desktop.\n35: \n36: ### Key Sources\n37: \n38: - [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - the primary CLI surface (binary identity, connect modes, daemon model) for authoring and exporting in Figma.\n39: - [tool_surface.md](tool_surface.md) - the CLI command gating taxonomy; the MCP path here is a separate, opt-in read surface, not part of that gating.\n40: - Code Mode mechanics (naming, prefixed env, discovery): [mcp-code-mode SKILL.md](../../mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md).\n41: \n42: Claims are tagged **[CONFIRMED]** (read from this repo's `.utcp_config.json` this session, or from the cited research digests) or **[INFERRED]** (reasoned, needs a live `tool_info()` / `list_tools()` to fix the exact string). The Framelink tool **names and input schemas are [INFERRED]** until a live discovery call confirms them, because the community server's per-tool schema is not pinned in this repo.\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## 2. THE REGISTERED `figma` MANUAL\n47: \n48: The `figma` manual is already present in `.utcp_config.json` under `manual_call_templates[]`. Read it before changing anything. **[CONFIRMED — read from `.utcp_config.json` this session]**\n49: \n50: ```json\n51: {\n52:   \"name\": \"figma\",\n53:   \"call_template_type\": \"mcp\",\n54:   \"config\": {\n55:     \"mcpServers\": {\n56:       \"figma\": {\n57:         \"transport\": \"stdio\",\n58:         \"command\": \"npx\",\n59:         \"args\": [\"-y\", \"figma-developer-mcp@latest\", \"--stdio\"],\n60:         \"env\": { \"FIGMA_API_KEY\": \"${FIGMA_API_KEY}\" }\n61:       }\n62:     }\n63:   }\n64: }\n65: ```\n66: \n67: What it provides: the Framelink `figma-developer-mcp` server (npm `figma-developer-mcp`, v0.12.0 confirmed published) wraps the Figma REST API and **simplifies Figma file data for coding agents** — i.e. design context an agent can turn into code. **[CONFIRMED — research digest, npm view]** It is a **third-party** server, not Figma's official MCP. **[CONFIRMED]**\n68: \n69: Transport is **stdio** over `npx`, which matches every other manual registered here (`chrome_devtools_1/2`, `clickup_official`, `github` are all stdio). No HTTP manual exists in this repo, so the stdio Framelink path is the proven one. **[CONFIRMED — `.utcp_config.json` inspection]**\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ## 3. THE `.env` TOKEN (prefixed)\n74: \n75: The manual's config references `${FIGMA_API_KEY}`, but **Code Mode prefixes every environment variable with the manual name**. So the `.env` entry must be the **prefixed** form, not the bare name. **[CONFIRMED — mcp-code-mode SKILL.md §4 \"Critical: Prefixed Environment Variables\"]**\n76: \n77: ```bash\n78: # .env (project root)\n79: figma_FIGMA_API_KEY=figd_your_token_here\n80: ```\n81: \n82: - The token is a **Figma personal access token** (begins `figd_`). Generate it in Figma → Settings → Security → personal access tokens. **[INFERRED — standard Figma token shape; verify in Figma]**\n83: - Using bare `FIGMA_API_KEY=...` will fail with `Error: Variable 'figma_FIGMA_API_KEY' not found`. **[CONFIRMED — mcp-code-mode SKILL.md §4]**\n84: - This is the **only** setup the MCP path needs — the manual is already registered (Section 2). Never paste the token into user-facing output; treat it as a credential.\n85: \n86: | Manual name | Config reference   | `.env` variable        |\n87: | ----------- | ------------------ | ---------------------- |\n88: | `figma`     | `${FIGMA_API_KEY}` | `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`  |\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## 4. DISCOVER FIRST\n93: \n94: Code Mode loads tools progressively. Always discover before calling, because the Framelink tool names and input schemas are not pinned in this repo and the `figma-developer-mcp@latest` surface can change. **[INFERRED — server is `@latest`; names unverified here]**\n95: \n96: ```typescript\n97: // 1) Is the figma manual present, and what tools does it expose?\n98: const all = await list_tools();\n99: // group returned names by the prefix before the first dot; look for the \"figma\" group\n100: \n101: // 2) Search by intent to find the right Figma tool\n102: const tools = await search_tools({\n103:   task_description: \"get figma file or node design data for code generation\",\n104:   limit: 10\n105: });\n106: \n107: // 3) Confirm the exact callable syntax + input schema before invoking\n108: const info = await tool_info({ tool_name: \"figma.figma_get_figma_data\" });\n109: ```\n110: \n111: **Confirmed live surface (2026-06-14 `list_tools()`):** the `figma` manual currently exposes exactly two tools — **`figma.figma_get_figma_data`** (fetch a file/node's design data) and **`figma.figma_download_figma_images`** (download referenced images/SVGs). **[CONFIRMED — live Code Mode `list_tools()`]** Always re-run discovery, since `figma-developer-mcp@latest` can change its surface; treat input schemas as `tool_info()`-verified, not assumed.\n112: \n113: `list_tools()` returns names in dotted (`a.b.c`) form; the **callable** form uses an underscore between the manual prefix and the tool: `figma.figma_<tool>`. `tool_info()` shows the correct calling syntax and the expected params. **[CONFIRMED — mcp-code-mode SKILL.md §3 naming + tool-name translation]**\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ## 5. CALL EXAMPLE (`call_tool_chain`)\n118: \n119: > Illustrative — the exact tool name and params are placeholders. Run `tool_info()` (Section 4) to fix `<tool>` and its arguments before relying on this.\n120: \n121: Naming pattern is `{manual}.{manual}_{tool}`, so every Framelink call is `figma.figma_<tool>`. Wrap calls in try/catch and return structured state. **[CONFIRMED — mcp-code-mode SKILL.md §3]**\n122: \n123: ```typescript\n124: await call_tool_chain({\n125:   code: `\n126:     try {\n127:       // Tool name confirmed via list_tools(); confirm the param schema with tool_info() first.\n128:       const file = await figma.figma_get_figma_data({\n129:         // fileKey / nodeId pulled from a Figma design URL:\n130:         // https://www.figma.com/design/FILE_KEY/Name?node-id=NODE_ID\n131:         fileKey: \"FILE_KEY\",\n132:         nodeId: \"NODE_ID\",\n133:         context: \"Pull Figma node data to generate a matching component\"\n134:       });\n135:       return { success: true, source: \"figma_framelink\", file };\n136:     } catch (err) {\n137:       return { success: false, error: String(err) };\n138:     }\n139:   `\n140: });\n141: ```\n142: \n143: Notes:\n144: \n145: - The Framelink server reads Figma via the REST API using the `.env` token — Figma Desktop does **not** need to be open for the MCP path (that requirement is the CLI's, not the MCP's). **[INFERRED — Framelink is API-backed, not Desktop-backed]**\n146: - Static manuals registered in `.utcp_config.json` need no cleanup; only dynamically registered manuals (`register_manual`) require `deregister_manual`. **[CONFIRMED — research digest IT2]**\n147: - MCP responses can be token-heavy. Prefer narrow, node-scoped calls over whole-file pulls when the schema allows it. **[CONFIRMED — research digest IT2 gotchas]**\n148: \n149: ---\n150: \n151: ## 6. OFFICIAL FIGMA DEV MODE MCP (out of scope this release)\n152: \n153: Figma also ships an **official** Dev Mode MCP server (a remote `https://mcp.figma.com/mcp` server and a desktop-local `http://127.0.0.1:3845/mcp` server, both HTTP MCP with OAuth/desktop-session auth). **[CONFIRMED — research digest IT2]** It is **not a supported path in this release** and is **not documented here**:\n154: \n155: - Code Mode has **no HTTP manual registered** in this repo — every manual is stdio — so the official HTTP transport is unproven here. **[CONFIRMED — `.utcp_config.json` inspection]**\n156: - The remote server is **catalog/OAuth-gated**; whether this project's Code Mode client is admitted is **unverified**. **[CONFIRMED — research digest IT2 unknowns]**\n157: \n158: Treat the official Dev Mode MCP as a **future option only**. Do not wire or recommend it as a supported route in this version; the registered Framelink `figma` manual (Sections 2–5) is the supported MCP path for now.\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ## 7. REFERENCES\n163: \n164: - [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - the primary CLI surface: binary identity, connect modes, daemon model, and command examples.\n165: - [tool_surface.md](tool_surface.md) - the CLI read-only / mutating / destructive taxonomy and gating.\n166: - [troubleshooting.md](troubleshooting.md) - failures including the Code Mode env-var prefix (`figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`) and tools-not-discovered cases.\n167: - [utcp_figma_manual.md](../assets/utcp_figma_manual.md) - the runnable Code Mode manual companion (the `figma` manual entry and ready-to-run `call_tool_chain` snippets).\n168: - [SKILL.md](../SKILL.md) - the skill contract these references support; see §3 \"Optional Figma MCP via Code Mode\".\n169: - Code Mode mechanics (naming, prefixed env, discovery): [mcp-code-mode SKILL.md](../../mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md).\n\n(End of file - total 169 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Figma MCP Wiring (optional, via Code Mode)\"\ndescription: \"Wiring the OPTIONAL Figma MCP into this project's Code Mode: the already-registered Framelink figma manual, the prefixed .env token, the discover-first flow, and a runnable call_tool_chain example. The CLI works fully alone; the MCP is opt-in.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma mcp\"\n  - \"figma mcp code mode\"\n  - \"figma-developer-mcp\"\n  - \"pull figma design context\"\n  - \"figma get_design_context\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n\n# Figma MCP Wiring (optional, via Code Mode)\n\n> **IMPORTANT:** This skill works **fully with the `figma-ds-cli` alone** — the MCP is **opt-in**. Before invoking any Figma MCP tool, always **discover first** (`search_tools` / `tool_info`) and confirm the `figma` manual and its exact tool names are present. Never guess a tool name, and never claim the MCP works until discovery confirms it.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Figma MCP Wiring (optional, via Code Mode)\"\ndescription: \"Wiring the OPTIONAL Figma MCP into this project's Code Mode: the already-registered Framelink figma manual, the prefixed .env token, the discover-first flow, and a runnable call_tool_chain example. The CLI works fully alone; the MCP is opt-in.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma mcp\"\n  - \"figma mcp code mode\"\n  - \"figma-developer-mcp\"\n  - \"pull figma design context\"\n  - \"figma get_design_context\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n\n# Figma MCP Wiring (optional, via Code Mode)\n\n> **IMPORTANT:** This skill works **fully with the `figma-ds-cli` alone** — the MCP is **opt-in**. Before invoking any Figma MCP tool, always **discover first** (`search_tools` / `tool_info`) and confirm the `figma` manual and its exact tool names are present. Never guess a tool name, and never claim the MCP works until discovery confirms it.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Core Principle\n\nWiring here means the agent reaches Figma's **read** surface — design context, variables, metadata — through this project's **Code Mode** transport. The Code Mode manual named `figma` is **already registered** in `.utcp_config.json` (community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp`, stdio, `npx`); nothing new needs to be installed for the MCP path. The only setup step is a `.env` entry with a Figma personal access token.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Pull Figma file/node data into the agent so it can generate or reconcile code against a design.\n- The work is codegen-from-design, not authoring or exporting from the live Desktop session.\n\nThe CLI vs MCP routing line:\n\n- **`figma-ds-cli` (CLI) = author/modify/export IN Figma.** It drives the live Figma Desktop session to create/render/modify nodes, manage tokens and variables, and export assets/JSX/CSS/screenshots. This is the primary surface.\n- **Figma MCP (Code Mode) = pull design data INTO the agent for codegen.** Use it only when the agent needs Figma design context as model input (file/node data, variables, screenshots) to generate or align code. The MCP does not drive Figma Desktop.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n- [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - the primary CLI surface (binary identity, connect modes, daemon model) for authoring and exporting in Figma.\n- [tool_surface.md](tool_surface.md) - the CLI command gating taxonomy; the MCP path here is a separate, opt-in read surface, not part of that gating.\n- Code Mode mechanics (naming, prefixed env, discovery): [mcp-code-mode SKILL.md](../../mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md).\n\nClaims are tagged **[CONFIRMED]** (read from this repo's `.utcp_config.json` this session, or from the cited research digests) or **[INFERRED]** (reasoned, needs a live `tool_info()` / `list_tools()` to fix the exact string). The Framelink tool **names and input schemas are [INFERRED]** until a live discovery call confirms them, because the community server's per-tool schema is not pinned in this repo.\n\n---\n\n## 2. THE REGISTERED `figma` MANUAL\n\nThe `figma` manual is already present in `.utcp_config.json` under `manual_call_templates[]`. Read it before changing anything. **[CONFIRMED — read from `.utcp_config.json` this session]**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"figma\",\n  \"call_template_type\": \"mcp\",\n  \"config\": {\n    \"mcpServers\": {\n      \"figma\": {\n        \"transport\": \"stdio\",\n        \"command\": \"npx\",\n        \"args\": [\"-y\", \"figma-developer-mcp@latest\", \"--stdio\"],\n        \"env\": { \"FIGMA_API_KEY\": \"${FIGMA_API_KEY}\" }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nWhat it provides: the Framelink `figma-developer-mcp` server (npm `figma-developer-mcp`, v0.12.0 confirmed published) wraps the Figma REST API and **simplifies Figma file data for coding agents** — i.e. design context an agent can turn into code. **[CONFIRMED — research digest, npm view]** It is a **third-party** server, not Figma's official MCP. **[CONFIRMED]**\n\nTransport is **stdio** over `npx`, which matches every other manual registered here (`chrome_devtools_1/2`, `clickup_official`, `github` are all stdio). No HTTP manual exists in this repo, so the stdio Framelink path is the proven one. **[CONFIRMED — `.utcp_config.json` inspection]**\n\n---\n\n## 3. THE `.env` TOKEN (prefixed)\n\nThe manual's config references `${FIGMA_API_KEY}`, but **Code Mode prefixes every environment variable with the manual name**. So the `.env` entry must be the **prefixed** form, not the bare name. **[CONFIRMED — mcp-code-mode SKILL.md §4 \"Critical: Prefixed Environment Variables\"]**\n\n```bash\n# .env (project root)\nfigma_FIGMA_API_KEY=figd_your_token_here\n```\n\n- The token is a **Figma personal access token** (begins `figd_`). Generate it in Figma → Settings → Security → personal access tokens. **[INFERRED — standard Figma token shape; verify in Figma]**\n- Using bare `FIGMA_API_KEY=...` will fail with `Error: Variable 'figma_FIGMA_API_KEY' not found`. **[CONFIRMED — mcp-code-mode SKILL.md §4]**\n- This is the **only** setup the MCP path needs — the manual is already registered (Section 2). Never paste the token into user-facing output; treat it as a credential.\n\n| Manual name | Config reference   | `.env` variable        |\n| ----------- | ------------------ | ---------------------- |\n| `figma`     | `${FIGMA_API_KEY}` | `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`  |\n\n---\n\n## 4. DISCOVER FIRST\n\nCode Mode loads tools progressively. Always discover before calling, because the Framelink tool names and input schemas are not pinned in this repo and the `figma-developer-mcp@latest` surface can change. **[INFERRED — server is `@latest`; names unverified here]**\n\n```typescript\n// 1) Is the figma manual present, and what tools does it expose?\nconst all = await list_tools();\n// group returned names by the prefix before the first dot; look for the \"figma\" group\n\n// 2) Search by intent to find the right Figma tool\nconst tools = await search_tools({\n  task_description: \"get figma file or node design data for code generation\",\n  limit: 10\n});\n\n// 3) Confirm the exact callable syntax + input schema before invoking\nconst info = await tool_info({ tool_name: \"figma.figma_get_figma_data\" });\n```\n\n**Confirmed live surface (2026-06-14 `list_tools()`):** the `figma` manual currently exposes exactly two tools — **`figma.figma_get_figma_data`** (fetch a file/node's design data) and **`figma.figma_download_figma_images`** (download referenced images/SVGs). **[CONFIRMED — live Code Mode `list_tools()`]** Always re-run discovery, since `figma-developer-mcp@latest` can change its surface; treat input schemas as `tool_info()`-verified, not assumed.\n\n`list_tools()` returns names in dotted (`a.b.c`) form; the **callable** form uses an underscore between the manual prefix and the tool: `figma.figma_<tool>`. `tool_info()` shows the correct calling syntax and the expected params. **[CONFIRMED — mcp-code-mode SKILL.md §3 naming + tool-name translation]**\n\n---\n\n## 5. CALL EXAMPLE (`call_tool_chain`)\n\n> Illustrative — the exact tool name and params are placeholders. Run `tool_info()` (Section 4) to fix `<tool>` and its arguments before relying on this.\n\nNaming pattern is `{manual}.{manual}_{tool}`, so every Framelink call is `figma.figma_<tool>`. Wrap calls in try/catch and return structured state. **[CONFIRMED — mcp-code-mode SKILL.md §3]**\n\n```typescript\nawait call_tool_chain({\n  code: `\n    try {\n      // Tool name confirmed via list_tools(); confirm the param schema with tool_info() first.\n      const file = await figma.figma_get_figma_data({\n        // fileKey / nodeId pulled from a Figma design URL:\n        // https://www.figma.com/design/FILE_KEY/Name?node-id=NODE_ID\n        fileKey: \"FILE_KEY\",\n        nodeId: \"NODE_ID\",\n        context: \"Pull Figma node data to generate a matching component\"\n      });\n      return { success: true, source: \"figma_framelink\", file };\n    } catch (err) {\n      return { success: false, error: String(err) };\n    }\n  `\n});\n```\n\nNotes:\n\n- The Framelink server reads Figma via the REST API using the `.env` token — Figma Desktop does **not** need to be open for the MCP path (that requirement is the CLI's, not the MCP's). **[INFERRED — Framelink is API-backed, not Desktop-backed]**\n- Static manuals registered in `.utcp_config.json` need no cleanup; only dynamically registered manuals (`register_manual`) require `deregister_manual`. **[CONFIRMED — research digest IT2]**\n- MCP responses can be token-heavy. Prefer narrow, node-scoped calls over whole-file pulls when the schema allows it. **[CONFIRMED — research digest IT2 gotchas]**\n\n---\n\n## 6. OFFICIAL FIGMA DEV MODE MCP (out of scope this release)\n\nFigma also ships an **official** Dev Mode MCP server (a remote `https://mcp.figma.com/mcp` server and a desktop-local `http://127.0.0.1:3845/mcp` server, both HTTP MCP with OAuth/desktop-session auth). **[CONFIRMED — research digest IT2]** It is **not a supported path in this release** and is **not documented here**:\n\n- Code Mode has **no HTTP manual registered** in this repo — every manual is stdio — so the official HTTP transport is unproven here. **[CONFIRMED — `.utcp_config.json` inspection]**\n- The remote server is **catalog/OAuth-gated**; whether this project's Code Mode client is admitted is **unverified**. **[CONFIRMED — research digest IT2 unknowns]**\n\nTreat the official Dev Mode MCP as a **future option only**. Do not wire or recommend it as a supported route in this version; the registered Framelink `figma` manual (Sections 2–5) is the supported MCP path for now.\n\n---\n\n## 7. REFERENCES\n\n- [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - the primary CLI surface: binary identity, connect modes, daemon model, and command examples.\n- [tool_surface.md](tool_surface.md) - the CLI read-only / mutating / destructive taxonomy and gating.\n- [troubleshooting.md](troubleshooting.md) - failures including the Code Mode env-var prefix (`figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`) and tools-not-discovered cases.\n- [utcp_figma_manual.md](../assets/utcp_figma_manual.md) - the runnable Code Mode manual companion (the `figma` manual entry and ready-to-run `call_tool_chain` snippets).\n- [SKILL.md](../SKILL.md) - the skill contract these references support; see §3 \"Optional Figma MCP via Code Mode\".\n- Code Mode mechanics (naming, prefixed env, discovery): [mcp-code-mode SKILL.md](../../mcp-code-mode/SKILL.md).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":169,"totalLines":169,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md","time":{"start":1781459286564,"end":1781459286569}},"id":"prt_ec73f78a2001sIus1Ai0m9NMY5","sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","messageID":"msg_ec73f6cdd001Qt6XwQnsx9f72T"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781459286983,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_8H3E7Ho5OzTrp3gZ0Q4d1353","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/assets/utcp_figma_manual.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/assets/utcp_figma_manual.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Figma Code Mode Manual - Framelink figma snippet\n3: description: Paste-ready .utcp_config.json manual entry plus .env note for the optional community Framelink figma MCP via Code Mode.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"figma code mode manual\"\n6:   - \"framelink figma utcp config\"\n7:   - \"figma developer mcp snippet\"\n8:   - \"figma mcp env key\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Figma Code Mode Manual - Framelink figma snippet\n14: \n15: Paste-ready `.utcp_config.json` manual entry and the matching `.env` note for the OPTIONAL community Framelink `figma` MCP, wired through this project's Code Mode.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: ### Purpose\n22: \n23: The mcp-figma skill works fully with the `figma-ds-cli` alone. This asset is for the opt-in path only: when the agent must pull design context FROM Figma (design data, variables, screenshots) as model input. It packages the community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp` manual entry (stdio) and its prefixed `.env` key so the manual can be added to Code Mode's `.utcp_config.json`.\n24: \n25: This is the community Framelink MCP, not the official Figma Dev Mode MCP server. The official Dev Mode MCP stays out of scope (future option only) and must not be promoted as the wiring here.\n26: \n27: ### Usage\n28: \n29: Add the manual object below into the `manual_call_templates` array of the project's `.utcp_config.json`, then put the prefixed key in `.env` (see [env_template.md](./env_template.md)). Code Mode names the manual `figma`, so calls are `figma.figma_<tool>` via `call_tool_chain()`, and the env var is prefixed `figma_`. Always discover the live surface with `search_tools()` / `tool_info()` before invoking — do not assume a tool exists.\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. UTCP MANUAL ENTRY\n34: \n35: **Key Points**:\n36: - Manual `name` is `figma` → call namespace is `figma.figma_<tool>` and env prefix is `figma_`.\n37: - Transport is `stdio`; the server is the community `figma-developer-mcp` (Framelink), launched on demand via `npx`.\n38: - The server needs a Figma personal access token, referenced as `${FIGMA_API_KEY}` and supplied in `.env` as `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`.\n39: - Live-confirmed tools are `get_figma_data` and `download_figma_images`; verify the rest of the surface at runtime.\n40: \n41: **Template** (add to `manual_call_templates` in `.utcp_config.json`):\n42: \n43: ```json\n44: {\n45:   \"name\": \"figma\",\n46:   \"call_template_type\": \"mcp\",\n47:   \"config\": {\n48:     \"mcpServers\": {\n49:       \"figma\": {\n50:         \"transport\": \"stdio\",\n51:         \"command\": \"npx\",\n52:         \"args\": [\"-y\", \"figma-developer-mcp\", \"--stdio\"],\n53:         \"env\": {\n54:           \"FIGMA_API_KEY\": \"${FIGMA_API_KEY}\"\n55:         }\n56:       }\n57:     }\n58:   }\n59: }\n60: ```\n61: \n62: **Field Guidelines**:\n63: \n64: **`name`**:\n65: - Manual namespace. Keep it `figma` so calls resolve as `figma.figma_<tool>` and env vars resolve as `figma_<VAR>`.\n66: \n67: **`args`**:\n68: - `[\"-y\", \"figma-developer-mcp\", \"--stdio\"]` runs the Framelink server on demand over stdio. The `-y` flag avoids an interactive npx prompt.\n69: \n70: **`env.FIGMA_API_KEY`**:\n71: - References `${FIGMA_API_KEY}`. Code Mode prefixes it with the manual name, so the actual `.env` key is `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`.\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## 3. .ENV NOTE\n76: \n77: **Key Points**:\n78: - Code Mode prefixes every env var with `{manual_name}_`. With manual `figma`, the `.env` key is `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` (NOT bare `FIGMA_API_KEY`).\n79: - The value is a Figma personal access token from Figma → Settings → Account → Personal Access Tokens.\n80: - Never commit `.env`; never paste the token into user-facing output.\n81: \n82: **Template** (add to `.env`):\n83: \n84: ```bash\n85: # Figma (Code Mode prefixes env vars with the manual name \"figma\")\n86: figma_FIGMA_API_KEY=figd_your_token_here\n87: ```\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## 4. CALL EXAMPLE\n92: \n93: **Discover first, then call** through Code Mode's `call_tool_chain()`:\n94: \n95: ```typescript\n96: call_tool_chain({\n97:   code: `\n98:     // 1) Confirm the manual + tool names exist before relying on them.\n99:     const info = await tool_info({ tool_name: \"figma.figma_get_figma_data\" });\n100:     // 2) Live-confirmed read tool: pull design data for a file/node.\n101:     const data = await figma.figma_get_figma_data({ fileKey: \"<file-key>\" });\n102:     return { ok: true, info };\n103:   `\n104: });\n105: ```\n106: \n107: The other live-confirmed tool is `figma.figma_download_figma_images` (export node images). Treat both as read-only context pulls; the CLI (`figma-ds-cli`) remains the surface for any authoring or mutation.\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ## 5. RELATED RESOURCES\n112: \n113: - [env_template.md](./env_template.md) - The prefixed `.env` line for the Figma token.\n114: - [mcp_wiring.md](../references/mcp_wiring.md) - The full optional Figma MCP wiring reference (discovery, gating, Code Mode env-var prefix).\n\n(End of file - total 114 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Figma Code Mode Manual - Framelink figma snippet\ndescription: Paste-ready .utcp_config.json manual entry plus .env note for the optional community Framelink figma MCP via Code Mode.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma code mode manual\"\n  - \"framelink figma utcp config\"\n  - \"figma developer mcp snippet\"\n  - \"figma mcp env key\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Figma Code Mode Manual - Framelink figma snippet\n\nPaste-ready `.utcp_config.json` manual entry and the matching `.env` note for the OPTIONAL community Framelink `figma` MCP, wired through this project's Code Mode.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/assets/utcp_figma_manual.md","text":"---\ntitle: Figma Code Mode Manual - Framelink figma snippet\ndescription: Paste-ready .utcp_config.json manual entry plus .env note for the optional community Framelink figma MCP via Code Mode.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma code mode manual\"\n  - \"framelink figma utcp config\"\n  - \"figma developer mcp snippet\"\n  - \"figma mcp env key\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Figma Code Mode Manual - Framelink figma snippet\n\nPaste-ready `.utcp_config.json` manual entry and the matching `.env` note for the OPTIONAL community Framelink `figma` MCP, wired through this project's Code Mode.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThe mcp-figma skill works fully with the `figma-ds-cli` alone. This asset is for the opt-in path only: when the agent must pull design context FROM Figma (design data, variables, screenshots) as model input. It packages the community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp` manual entry (stdio) and its prefixed `.env` key so the manual can be added to Code Mode's `.utcp_config.json`.\n\nThis is the community Framelink MCP, not the official Figma Dev Mode MCP server. The official Dev Mode MCP stays out of scope (future option only) and must not be promoted as the wiring here.\n\n### Usage\n\nAdd the manual object below into the `manual_call_templates` array of the project's `.utcp_config.json`, then put the prefixed key in `.env` (see [env_template.md](./env_template.md)). Code Mode names the manual `figma`, so calls are `figma.figma_<tool>` via `call_tool_chain()`, and the env var is prefixed `figma_`. Always discover the live surface with `search_tools()` / `tool_info()` before invoking — do not assume a tool exists.\n\n---\n\n## 2. UTCP MANUAL ENTRY\n\n**Key Points**:\n- Manual `name` is `figma` → call namespace is `figma.figma_<tool>` and env prefix is `figma_`.\n- Transport is `stdio`; the server is the community `figma-developer-mcp` (Framelink), launched on demand via `npx`.\n- The server needs a Figma personal access token, referenced as `${FIGMA_API_KEY}` and supplied in `.env` as `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`.\n- Live-confirmed tools are `get_figma_data` and `download_figma_images`; verify the rest of the surface at runtime.\n\n**Template** (add to `manual_call_templates` in `.utcp_config.json`):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"figma\",\n  \"call_template_type\": \"mcp\",\n  \"config\": {\n    \"mcpServers\": {\n      \"figma\": {\n        \"transport\": \"stdio\",\n        \"command\": \"npx\",\n        \"args\": [\"-y\", \"figma-developer-mcp\", \"--stdio\"],\n        \"env\": {\n          \"FIGMA_API_KEY\": \"${FIGMA_API_KEY}\"\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Field Guidelines**:\n\n**`name`**:\n- Manual namespace. Keep it `figma` so calls resolve as `figma.figma_<tool>` and env vars resolve as `figma_<VAR>`.\n\n**`args`**:\n- `[\"-y\", \"figma-developer-mcp\", \"--stdio\"]` runs the Framelink server on demand over stdio. The `-y` flag avoids an interactive npx prompt.\n\n**`env.FIGMA_API_KEY`**:\n- References `${FIGMA_API_KEY}`. Code Mode prefixes it with the manual name, so the actual `.env` key is `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. .ENV NOTE\n\n**Key Points**:\n- Code Mode prefixes every env var with `{manual_name}_`. With manual `figma`, the `.env` key is `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` (NOT bare `FIGMA_API_KEY`).\n- The value is a Figma personal access token from Figma → Settings → Account → Personal Access Tokens.\n- Never commit `.env`; never paste the token into user-facing output.\n\n**Template** (add to `.env`):\n\n```bash\n# Figma (Code Mode prefixes env vars with the manual name \"figma\")\nfigma_FIGMA_API_KEY=figd_your_token_here\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. CALL EXAMPLE\n\n**Discover first, then call** through Code Mode's `call_tool_chain()`:\n\n```typescript\ncall_tool_chain({\n  code: `\n    // 1) Confirm the manual + tool names exist before relying on them.\n    const info = await tool_info({ tool_name: \"figma.figma_get_figma_data\" });\n    // 2) Live-confirmed read tool: pull design data for a file/node.\n    const data = await figma.figma_get_figma_data({ fileKey: \"<file-key>\" });\n    return { ok: true, info };\n  `\n});\n```\n\nThe other live-confirmed tool is `figma.figma_download_figma_images` (export node images). Treat both as read-only context pulls; the CLI (`figma-ds-cli`) remains the surface for any authoring or mutation.\n\n---\n\n## 5. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- [env_template.md](./env_template.md) - The prefixed `.env` line for the Figma token.\n- [mcp_wiring.md](../references/mcp_wiring.md) - The full optional Figma MCP wiring reference (discovery, gating, Code Mode env-var prefix).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":114,"totalLines":114,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/assets/utcp_figma_manual.md","time":{"start":1781459286979,"end":1781459286982}},"id":"prt_ec73f7a66001s4N7Sav32hylqq","sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","messageID":"msg_ec73f6cdd001Qt6XwQnsx9f72T"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781459287336,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_1xCNRBAaA0fmgKeMJzUy1514","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/assets/env_template.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/assets/env_template.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Figma Code Mode Env Template - prefixed token line\n3: description: The single prefixed .env line for the optional Framelink figma MCP token used by this project's Code Mode.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"figma env template\"\n6:   - \"figma api key prefixed\"\n7:   - \"figma code mode token\"\n8:   - \"figma_figma_api_key env\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Figma Code Mode Env Template - prefixed token line\n14: \n15: The single prefixed `.env` line that authenticates the OPTIONAL Framelink `figma` MCP through this project's Code Mode.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: ### Purpose\n22: \n23: The `figma-ds-cli` itself needs NO Figma API key — it drives the live Figma Desktop session. This env line is only for the opt-in Code Mode path that pulls design context FROM Figma via the community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp`. It exists so the token is supplied in the prefixed form Code Mode expects.\n24: \n25: ### Usage\n26: \n27: Copy the line below into the project `.env`, replace the placeholder with a Figma personal access token (Figma → Settings → Account → Personal Access Tokens), and never commit `.env`. The manual entry that consumes this key lives in [utcp_figma_manual.md](./utcp_figma_manual.md).\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## 2. ENV LINE\n32: \n33: **Key Points**:\n34: - Code Mode prefixes env vars with `{manual_name}_`. The Figma manual `name` is `figma`, so the key MUST be `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` (the bare `FIGMA_API_KEY` is not found by Code Mode).\n35: - The value is a Figma personal access token, shown only once at creation.\n36: - Keep all credentials out of version control and out of user-facing output.\n37: \n38: **Template** (add to `.env`):\n39: \n40: ```bash\n41: # Figma Configuration\n42: # (Code Mode prefixes all env vars with the manual name \"figma\" from .utcp_config.json)\n43: figma_FIGMA_API_KEY=figd_your_token_here\n44: ```\n45: \n46: **Field Guidelines**:\n47: \n48: **`figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`**:\n49: - Prefix `figma_` is the Code Mode manual name; `FIGMA_API_KEY` is the variable the manual references as `${FIGMA_API_KEY}`.\n50: - Format: a Figma personal access token, typically `figd_...`.\n51: - Required only for the optional Code Mode Figma MCP path; the CLI does not use it.\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 3. VERIFY\n56: \n57: Confirm the prefixed key is present before relying on the optional MCP:\n58: \n59: ```bash\n60: grep '_FIGMA_API_KEY' .env   # should show: figma_FIGMA_API_KEY=figd_...\n61: ```\n62: \n63: A bare `FIGMA_API_KEY=...` line will surface the Code Mode error \"Variable 'figma_FIGMA_API_KEY' ... not found\".\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## 4. RELATED RESOURCES\n68: \n69: - [utcp_figma_manual.md](./utcp_figma_manual.md) - The paste-ready `.utcp_config.json` manual entry that consumes this key.\n70: - [mcp_wiring.md](../references/mcp_wiring.md) - The optional Figma MCP wiring reference.\n\n(End of file - total 70 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Figma Code Mode Env Template - prefixed token line\ndescription: The single prefixed .env line for the optional Framelink figma MCP token used by this project's Code Mode.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma env template\"\n  - \"figma api key prefixed\"\n  - \"figma code mode token\"\n  - \"figma_figma_api_key env\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Figma Code Mode Env Template - prefixed token line\n\nThe single prefixed `.env` line that authenticates the OPTIONAL Framelink `figma` MCP through this project's Code Mode.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/assets/env_template.md","text":"---\ntitle: Figma Code Mode Env Template - prefixed token line\ndescription: The single prefixed .env line for the optional Framelink figma MCP token used by this project's Code Mode.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma env template\"\n  - \"figma api key prefixed\"\n  - \"figma code mode token\"\n  - \"figma_figma_api_key env\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Figma Code Mode Env Template - prefixed token line\n\nThe single prefixed `.env` line that authenticates the OPTIONAL Framelink `figma` MCP through this project's Code Mode.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nThe `figma-ds-cli` itself needs NO Figma API key — it drives the live Figma Desktop session. This env line is only for the opt-in Code Mode path that pulls design context FROM Figma via the community Framelink `figma-developer-mcp`. It exists so the token is supplied in the prefixed form Code Mode expects.\n\n### Usage\n\nCopy the line below into the project `.env`, replace the placeholder with a Figma personal access token (Figma → Settings → Account → Personal Access Tokens), and never commit `.env`. The manual entry that consumes this key lives in [utcp_figma_manual.md](./utcp_figma_manual.md).\n\n---\n\n## 2. ENV LINE\n\n**Key Points**:\n- Code Mode prefixes env vars with `{manual_name}_`. The Figma manual `name` is `figma`, so the key MUST be `figma_FIGMA_API_KEY` (the bare `FIGMA_API_KEY` is not found by Code Mode).\n- The value is a Figma personal access token, shown only once at creation.\n- Keep all credentials out of version control and out of user-facing output.\n\n**Template** (add to `.env`):\n\n```bash\n# Figma Configuration\n# (Code Mode prefixes all env vars with the manual name \"figma\" from .utcp_config.json)\nfigma_FIGMA_API_KEY=figd_your_token_here\n```\n\n**Field Guidelines**:\n\n**`figma_FIGMA_API_KEY`**:\n- Prefix `figma_` is the Code Mode manual name; `FIGMA_API_KEY` is the variable the manual references as `${FIGMA_API_KEY}`.\n- Format: a Figma personal access token, typically `figd_...`.\n- Required only for the optional Code Mode Figma MCP path; the CLI does not use it.\n\n---\n\n## 3. VERIFY\n\nConfirm the prefixed key is present before relying on the optional MCP:\n\n```bash\ngrep '_FIGMA_API_KEY' .env   # should show: figma_FIGMA_API_KEY=figd_...\n```\n\nA bare `FIGMA_API_KEY=...` line will surface the Code Mode error \"Variable 'figma_FIGMA_API_KEY' ... not found\".\n\n---\n\n## 4. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- [utcp_figma_manual.md](./utcp_figma_manual.md) - The paste-ready `.utcp_config.json` manual entry that consumes this key.\n- [mcp_wiring.md](../references/mcp_wiring.md) - The optional Figma MCP wiring reference.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":70,"totalLines":70,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/assets/env_template.md","time":{"start":1781459287329,"end":1781459287335}},"id":"prt_ec73f7c0a001wwvIJegk9xIevY","sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","messageID":"msg_ec73f6cdd001Qt6XwQnsx9f72T"}}
