{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1781459287659,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","part":{"id":"prt_ec73f7e69001P1vGoXM2tIWpD5","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"713576c1c89394d69527900874510264f66af1c6","messageID":"msg_ec73f6cdd001Qt6XwQnsx9f72T","sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":128573,"input":61,"output":220,"reasoning":36,"cache":{"write":0,"read":128256}},"cost":0.000714183}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781459289299,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","part":{"id":"prt_ec73f84d20010zmC9fC82a5EZ3","messageID":"msg_ec73f7f5b001xbG4nRXHMcbwE0","sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","snapshot":"713576c1c89394d69527900874510264f66af1c6","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781459295890,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_wdDpyq5uaQiVjKpBU4im4642","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/tool_surface.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/tool_surface.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Figma CLI Tool Surface\"\n3: description: \"The figma-ds-cli command surface classified read-only / mutating / destructive / arbitrary, plus the surface / gate / omit policy, the explicit destructive set with per-command rollback, the eval/raw/run arbitrary-mutation rule, the local-export no-overwrite rule, and the live --help verification requirement.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"figma cli command gating\"\n6:   - \"figma-ds-cli tool surface\"\n7:   - \"figma destructive commands\"\n8:   - \"figma read-only vs mutating\"\n9:   - \"figma eval raw run rule\"\n10: importance_tier: \"normal\"\n11: contextType: \"implementation\"\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Figma CLI Tool Surface\n15: \n16: > **IMPORTANT:** This taxonomy was built from a read-only source scan of the silships `figma-cli` repo (`main`, package `figma-ds-cli@1.2.0`) plus its `REFERENCE.md` / `CLAUDE.md`. The command surface **drifts** between `REFERENCE.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, and the actual `src/commands/*.js` (documented commands such as `voice`, `chat`, `prop combine`, and the `create rect/circle/...` primitives were NOT found in the source scan). **Always verify a command with `<bin> <command> --help` before relying on it**, and gate every mutating or destructive verb. The CLI was not installed or executed during this analysis, so every example below is **illustrative; verify with `--help`**.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Core Principle\n23: \n24: Surface read-only commands freely, gate every mutating verb behind confirmation plus an explicit target plus a one-line rollback, treat the explicit destructive set as the strictest case (confirm + explicit target + rollback, prefer duplicate-first), and treat `eval` / `raw` / `run` as arbitrary mutation that must be reviewed before it runs. The canonical binary is **`figma-ds-cli`**; the source surface is the only source of truth and it drifts from the docs.\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: \n28: - Decide whether a `figma-ds-cli` command is safe to call unprompted, must be gated, or is destructive and needs confirmation plus a rollback.\n29: - Confirm the gating class of any command before authoring, modifying, deleting, or exporting in a Figma document.\n30: - Reach for the destructive set and rollback table before any delete / clear / undo / unwrap / uninstall / unlink operation.\n31: \n32: ### Key Sources\n33: \n34: - [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - the binary identity, connect modes, daemon model, and command examples.\n35: - [mcp_wiring.md](mcp_wiring.md) - the optional Framelink Figma MCP via Code Mode (a separate, opt-in surface, not part of this CLI gating).\n36: \n37: Claims here are tagged **READ-ONLY**, **MUTATING**, **DESTRUCTIVE**, or **ARBITRARY** as defined in Section 2, and were read from the repo source scan recorded in the packet research digest (`151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support/001-figma-cli-and-mcp-research`). They are **source-verified for repo `main`**, not live-verified against an installed binary.\n38: \n39: ### The naming trap (read first)\n40: \n41: The canonical binary is **`figma-ds-cli`** (silships, npm `figma-ds-cli`, MIT). The npm package literally named **`figma-cli` is an UNRELATED tool** (unic/figma-cli, bin `figma`). **NEVER `npm i -g figma-cli`.** The `figma-cli` command only exists when installed from the silships repo (`main` exposes both `figma-ds-cli` and `figma-cli`); npm `latest` (`1.0.0`) exposes only `figma-ds-cli`. This document writes every command with `figma-ds-cli`.\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## 2. THE FOUR CLASSES\n46: \n47: Every command falls into exactly one gating class. The class drives the exposure policy in Section 4.\n48: \n49: - **READ-ONLY** — reads Figma or local state, or writes an **export file**, without changing the Figma document or app/config state. Safe to surface. **Caveat:** any command that writes a local file (`extract`, `export*`, `verify --save`, `analyze-url --screenshot`, `api setup/index`) must use an **explicit output path and never silently overwrite** an existing file (see Section 5).\n50: - **MUTATING** — changes the Figma document, the current selection, or local tool / app / plugin / config state. Gate behind confirmation + an explicit target + a one-line rollback. Includes all authoring, layout, token, binding, variant, import, app-level connect/patch/daemon, and `init-agent` verbs.\n51: - **DESTRUCTIVE** — deletes Figma document content, variables, collections, annotations, grids, or removes an installed/local resource. The strictest case: confirm + **explicit target** + a stated rollback, and **prefer duplicating** the file/page/selection first. Never via an active-selection fallback. The explicit set + per-command rollback is Section 6.\n52: - **ARBITRARY** — `eval`, `run`, and `raw` execute arbitrary Figma Plugin API code or arbitrary `figma-use` commands. They can do **anything** (read, mutate, or delete). Treat as MUTATING-at-minimum, **review the code/command before running**, and never run them on an exploratory hunch (Section 7).\n53: \n54: > Tag meanings used in the table below: `READ-ONLY`, `MUTATING`, `DESTRUCTIVE`, `ARBITRARY`. Where a single command name has read-only and write sub-verbs (`component prop`, `dev`, `section`, `grid`, `annotate`), the per-sub-verb class is called out.\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 3. THE COMMAND SURFACE (CLASSIFIED BY GROUP)\n59: \n60: Source-verified against repo `main` `src/commands/*.js`, `REFERENCE.md`, and `CLAUDE.md`. **Verify with `--help` before relying on any row** — the surface drifts (Section 8).\n61: \n62: | Group | Command | Class | Notes |\n63: | ----- | ------- | ----- | ----- |\n64: | Setup | `figma-ds-cli` (first run) | MUTATING | First-run wizard: checks Node, may patch Figma, starts Figma. App-level. |\n65: | Setup | `init` / `setup` | MUTATING | Interactive setup; `setup` aliases `init`. App-level. |\n66: | Setup | `connect [--safe]` | MUTATING | `--safe` = plugin bridge (no patch, DEFAULT). Bare `connect` = yolo `app.asar` patch (GATE: consent + rollback). App-level. |\n67: | Setup | `unpatch` | MUTATING | Restores the original `app.asar` string (the yolo rollback). App-level. |\n68: | Setup | `status` | READ-ONLY | Checks CDP + daemon status. |\n69: | Setup | `diagnose` | READ-ONLY | System compatibility + connection status. |\n70: | Daemon | `daemon status [--debug]` | READ-ONLY | Daemon health / token diagnostics. |\n71: | Daemon | `daemon diagnose` | READ-ONLY | Full daemon troubleshooting. |\n72: | Daemon | `daemon start [--force]` | MUTATING | Starts daemon, generates token. App-level. |\n73: | Daemon | `daemon stop` | MUTATING | Stops daemon. App-level. |\n74: | Daemon | `daemon restart` | MUTATING | Restarts daemon, regenerates token. App-level. |\n75: | Daemon | `daemon reconnect` | MUTATING | Reconnects daemon to Figma. App-level. |\n76: | Agent setup | `init-agent [--tool claude\\|cursor\\|both] [--force]` | MUTATING | Writes `AGENTS.md` and/or `.cursor/rules/figma-cli.mdc` into the **working repo**. Not default-run. |\n77: | Design I/O | `extract [output] [--pages] [--sections] [--selection] [--split\\|--no-split]` | READ-ONLY | Writes `DESIGN.md`; auto-splits large structure into `DESIGN-structure/`. Explicit output path; no overwrite. |\n78: | Design I/O | `spec <component> [-f file] [--check nodeId] [--tolerance px]` | READ-ONLY | Reads `DESIGN.md` spec; `--check` measures a built node, non-zero exit on mismatch. |\n79: | Design I/O | `import <source> [-c] [--save] [--type ...] [--print-context]` | MUTATING | Imports DESIGN.md / Tailwind / CSS / tokens.json / Storybook into variables. |\n80: | Variables | `var list` / `var find <pattern>` | READ-ONLY | Lists / finds variables. |\n81: | Variables | `var visualize [collection]` | MUTATING | Creates color swatches on canvas. |\n82: | Variables | `var create <name> ...` / `var create-batch <json> -c` | MUTATING | Creates one / many variables. |\n83: | Variables | `var bind-batch <json>` / `var set-batch <json>` / `var rename-batch <json>` | MUTATING | Batch bind / set / rename across nodes. |\n84: | Variables | `var delete-all [-c collection]` | **DESTRUCTIVE** | Deletes all local variables/collections (or one collection's). |\n85: | Variables | `var delete-batch <nodeIds>` | **DESTRUCTIVE** | Deletes multiple nodes by id. |\n86: | Collections | `collections list` / `col list` | READ-ONLY | Lists collections. |\n87: | Collections | `collections create <name>` / `col create <name>` | MUTATING | Creates a collection. |\n88: | Tokens | `tokens overlap <collections...> [--json]` | READ-ONLY | Compares token names across collections. |\n89: | Tokens | `tokens tailwind\\|preset\\|shadcn\\|spacing\\|radii\\|ds\\|components` | MUTATING | Creates token scales / presets / base design system. |\n90: | Tokens | `tokens import <file>` / `tokens import-design-md <file>` | MUTATING | Imports JSON / DESIGN.md tokens. |\n91: | Tokens | `tokens add <name> <value> [-c] [-t]` | MUTATING | Adds one token. |\n92: | Binding | `bind list [-t COLOR\\|FLOAT]` | READ-ONLY | Lists bindable variables. |\n93: | Binding | `bind fill\\|stroke\\|radius\\|gap\\|padding <varName> [-n] [-s]` | MUTATING | Binds a node property to a variable. |\n94: | Creation | `render <jsx> ...` / `render-batch <jsxArray> ...` | MUTATING | Renders JSX to Figma. Preferred over `eval` for visual nodes. |\n95: | Creation | `undo` | **DESTRUCTIVE** | Removes the node(s) created by the latest render / render-batch. |\n96: | Creation | `create frame\\|icon\\|image ...` | MUTATING | Creates a frame / Iconify icon / image-from-URL node. |\n97: | Creation | `rect\\|ellipse\\|text\\|line\\|component\\|group\\|autolayout\\|al` | MUTATING | Top-level primitive aliases (source-proven; `REFERENCE.md` `create rect/...` form is drift — verify with `--help`). |\n98: | Layout | `sizing hug\\|fill\\|fixed ...` | MUTATING | Sets auto-layout sizing. |\n99: | Layout | `padding\\|pad` / `gap` / `align` | MUTATING | Sets padding / gap / alignment. |\n100: | Layout | `set autolayout\\|al ...` / `set pin <edge> ...` | MUTATING | Applies auto-layout / constraints. |\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 273. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Figma CLI Tool Surface\"\ndescription: \"The figma-ds-cli command surface classified read-only / mutating / destructive / arbitrary, plus the surface / gate / omit policy, the explicit destructive set with per-command rollback, the eval/raw/run arbitrary-mutation rule, the local-export no-overwrite rule, and the live --help verification requirement.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma cli command gating\"\n  - \"figma-ds-cli tool surface\"\n  - \"figma destructive commands\"\n  - \"figma read-only vs mutating\"\n  - \"figma eval raw run rule\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n\n# Figma CLI Tool Surface\n\n> **IMPORTANT:** This taxonomy was built from a read-only source scan of the silships `figma-cli` repo (`main`, package `figma-ds-cli@1.2.0`) plus its `REFERENCE.md` / `CLAUDE.md`. The command surface **drifts** between `REFERENCE.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, and the actual `src/commands/*.js` (documented commands such as `voice`, `chat`, `prop combine`, and the `create rect/circle/...` primitives were NOT found in the source scan). **Always verify a command with `<bin> <command> --help` before relying on it**, and gate every mutating or destructive verb. The CLI was not installed or executed during this analysis, so every example below is **illustrative; verify with `--help`**.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/tool_surface.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Figma CLI Tool Surface\"\ndescription: \"The figma-ds-cli command surface classified read-only / mutating / destructive / arbitrary, plus the surface / gate / omit policy, the explicit destructive set with per-command rollback, the eval/raw/run arbitrary-mutation rule, the local-export no-overwrite rule, and the live --help verification requirement.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma cli command gating\"\n  - \"figma-ds-cli tool surface\"\n  - \"figma destructive commands\"\n  - \"figma read-only vs mutating\"\n  - \"figma eval raw run rule\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n\n# Figma CLI Tool Surface\n\n> **IMPORTANT:** This taxonomy was built from a read-only source scan of the silships `figma-cli` repo (`main`, package `figma-ds-cli@1.2.0`) plus its `REFERENCE.md` / `CLAUDE.md`. The command surface **drifts** between `REFERENCE.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, and the actual `src/commands/*.js` (documented commands such as `voice`, `chat`, `prop combine`, and the `create rect/circle/...` primitives were NOT found in the source scan). **Always verify a command with `<bin> <command> --help` before relying on it**, and gate every mutating or destructive verb. The CLI was not installed or executed during this analysis, so every example below is **illustrative; verify with `--help`**.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Core Principle\n\nSurface read-only commands freely, gate every mutating verb behind confirmation plus an explicit target plus a one-line rollback, treat the explicit destructive set as the strictest case (confirm + explicit target + rollback, prefer duplicate-first), and treat `eval` / `raw` / `run` as arbitrary mutation that must be reviewed before it runs. The canonical binary is **`figma-ds-cli`**; the source surface is the only source of truth and it drifts from the docs.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Decide whether a `figma-ds-cli` command is safe to call unprompted, must be gated, or is destructive and needs confirmation plus a rollback.\n- Confirm the gating class of any command before authoring, modifying, deleting, or exporting in a Figma document.\n- Reach for the destructive set and rollback table before any delete / clear / undo / unwrap / uninstall / unlink operation.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n- [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - the binary identity, connect modes, daemon model, and command examples.\n- [mcp_wiring.md](mcp_wiring.md) - the optional Framelink Figma MCP via Code Mode (a separate, opt-in surface, not part of this CLI gating).\n\nClaims here are tagged **READ-ONLY**, **MUTATING**, **DESTRUCTIVE**, or **ARBITRARY** as defined in Section 2, and were read from the repo source scan recorded in the packet research digest (`151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support/001-figma-cli-and-mcp-research`). They are **source-verified for repo `main`**, not live-verified against an installed binary.\n\n### The naming trap (read first)\n\nThe canonical binary is **`figma-ds-cli`** (silships, npm `figma-ds-cli`, MIT). The npm package literally named **`figma-cli` is an UNRELATED tool** (unic/figma-cli, bin `figma`). **NEVER `npm i -g figma-cli`.** The `figma-cli` command only exists when installed from the silships repo (`main` exposes both `figma-ds-cli` and `figma-cli`); npm `latest` (`1.0.0`) exposes only `figma-ds-cli`. This document writes every command with `figma-ds-cli`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. THE FOUR CLASSES\n\nEvery command falls into exactly one gating class. The class drives the exposure policy in Section 4.\n\n- **READ-ONLY** — reads Figma or local state, or writes an **export file**, without changing the Figma document or app/config state. Safe to surface. **Caveat:** any command that writes a local file (`extract`, `export*`, `verify --save`, `analyze-url --screenshot`, `api setup/index`) must use an **explicit output path and never silently overwrite** an existing file (see Section 5).\n- **MUTATING** — changes the Figma document, the current selection, or local tool / app / plugin / config state. Gate behind confirmation + an explicit target + a one-line rollback. Includes all authoring, layout, token, binding, variant, import, app-level connect/patch/daemon, and `init-agent` verbs.\n- **DESTRUCTIVE** — deletes Figma document content, variables, collections, annotations, grids, or removes an installed/local resource. The strictest case: confirm + **explicit target** + a stated rollback, and **prefer duplicating** the file/page/selection first. Never via an active-selection fallback. The explicit set + per-command rollback is Section 6.\n- **ARBITRARY** — `eval`, `run`, and `raw` execute arbitrary Figma Plugin API code or arbitrary `figma-use` commands. They can do **anything** (read, mutate, or delete). Treat as MUTATING-at-minimum, **review the code/command before running**, and never run them on an exploratory hunch (Section 7).\n\n> Tag meanings used in the table below: `READ-ONLY`, `MUTATING`, `DESTRUCTIVE`, `ARBITRARY`. Where a single command name has read-only and write sub-verbs (`component prop`, `dev`, `section`, `grid`, `annotate`), the per-sub-verb class is called out.\n\n---\n\n## 3. THE COMMAND SURFACE (CLASSIFIED BY GROUP)\n\nSource-verified against repo `main` `src/commands/*.js`, `REFERENCE.md`, and `CLAUDE.md`. **Verify with `--help` before relying on any row** — the surface drifts (Section 8).\n\n| Group | Command | Class | Notes |\n| ----- | ------- | ----- | ----- |\n| Setup | `figma-ds-cli` (first run) | MUTATING | First-run wizard: checks Node, may patch Figma, starts Figma. App-level. |\n| Setup | `init` / `setup` | MUTATING | Interactive setup; `setup` aliases `init`. App-level. |\n| Setup | `connect [--safe]` | MUTATING | `--safe` = plugin bridge (no patch, DEFAULT). Bare `connect` = yolo `app.asar` patch (GATE: consent + rollback). App-level. |\n| Setup | `unpatch` | MUTATING | Restores the original `app.asar` string (the yolo rollback). App-level. |\n| Setup | `status` | READ-ONLY | Checks CDP + daemon status. |\n| Setup | `diagnose` | READ-ONLY | System compatibility + connection status. |\n| Daemon | `daemon status [--debug]` | READ-ONLY | Daemon health / token diagnostics. |\n| Daemon | `daemon diagnose` | READ-ONLY | Full daemon troubleshooting. |\n| Daemon | `daemon start [--force]` | MUTATING | Starts daemon, generates token. App-level. |\n| Daemon | `daemon stop` | MUTATING | Stops daemon. App-level. |\n| Daemon | `daemon restart` | MUTATING | Restarts daemon, regenerates token. App-level. |\n| Daemon | `daemon reconnect` | MUTATING | Reconnects daemon to Figma. App-level. |\n| Agent setup | `init-agent [--tool claude\\|cursor\\|both] [--force]` | MUTATING | Writes `AGENTS.md` and/or `.cursor/rules/figma-cli.mdc` into the **working repo**. Not default-run. |\n| Design I/O | `extract [output] [--pages] [--sections] [--selection] [--split\\|--no-split]` | READ-ONLY | Writes `DESIGN.md`; auto-splits large structure into `DESIGN-structure/`. Explicit output path; no overwrite. |\n| Design I/O | `spec <component> [-f file] [--check nodeId] [--tolerance px]` | READ-ONLY | Reads `DESIGN.md` spec; `--check` measures a built node, non-zero exit on mismatch. |\n| Design I/O | `import <source> [-c] [--save] [--type ...] [--print-context]` | MUTATING | Imports DESIGN.md / Tailwind / CSS / tokens.json / Storybook into variables. |\n| Variables | `var list` / `var find <pattern>` | READ-ONLY | Lists / finds variables. |\n| Variables | `var visualize [collection]` | MUTATING | Creates color swatches on canvas. |\n| Variables | `var create <name> ...` / `var create-batch <json> -c` | MUTATING | Creates one / many variables. |\n| Variables | `var bind-batch <json>` / `var set-batch <json>` / `var rename-batch <json>` | MUTATING | Batch bind / set / rename across nodes. |\n| Variables | `var delete-all [-c collection]` | **DESTRUCTIVE** | Deletes all local variables/collections (or one collection's). |\n| Variables | `var delete-batch <nodeIds>` | **DESTRUCTIVE** | Deletes multiple nodes by id. |\n| Collections | `collections list` / `col list` | READ-ONLY | Lists collections. |\n| Collections | `collections create <name>` / `col create <name>` | MUTATING | Creates a collection. |\n| Tokens | `tokens overlap <collections...> [--json]` | READ-ONLY | Compares token names across collections. |\n| Tokens | `tokens tailwind\\|preset\\|shadcn\\|spacing\\|radii\\|ds\\|components` | MUTATING | Creates token scales / presets / base design system. |\n| Tokens | `tokens import <file>` / `tokens import-design-md <file>` | MUTATING | Imports JSON / DESIGN.md tokens. |\n| Tokens | `tokens add <name> <value> [-c] [-t]` | MUTATING | Adds one token. |\n| Binding | `bind list [-t COLOR\\|FLOAT]` | READ-ONLY | Lists bindable variables. |\n| Binding | `bind fill\\|stroke\\|radius\\|gap\\|padding <varName> [-n] [-s]` | MUTATING | Binds a node property to a variable. |\n| Creation | `render <jsx> ...` / `render-batch <jsxArray> ...` | MUTATING | Renders JSX to Figma. Preferred over `eval` for visual nodes. |\n| Creation | `undo` | **DESTRUCTIVE** | Removes the node(s) created by the latest render / render-batch. |\n| Creation | `create frame\\|icon\\|image ...` | MUTATING | Creates a frame / Iconify icon / image-from-URL node. |\n| Creation | `rect\\|ellipse\\|text\\|line\\|component\\|group\\|autolayout\\|al` | MUTATING | Top-level primitive aliases (source-proven; `REFERENCE.md` `create rect/...` form is drift — verify with `--help`). |\n| Layout | `sizing hug\\|fill\\|fixed ...` | MUTATING | Sets auto-layout sizing. |\n| Layout | `padding\\|pad` / `gap` / `align` | MUTATING | Sets padding / gap / alignment. |\n| Layout | `set autolayout\\|al ...` / `set pin <edge> ...` | MUTATING | Applies auto-layout / constraints. |","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":100,"totalLines":273,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/tool_surface.md","time":{"start":1781459295886,"end":1781459295889}},"id":"prt_ec73f9cbd0011CW77lH8Gzi07y","sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","messageID":"msg_ec73f7f5b001xbG4nRXHMcbwE0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781459296409,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_HC7xmzUudeZgOaROSd5w5102","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md","limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Figma CLI Troubleshooting\"\n3: description: \"Symptom to cause to fix guide for common figma-ds-cli, daemon, connect, and optional Code Mode MCP issues.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"figma-cli command not found\"\n6:   - \"figma-ds-cli troubleshooting\"\n7:   - \"figma daemon unauthorized\"\n8:   - \"figma connect safe mode\"\n9:   - \"figma yolo patch broke\"\n10:   - \"figma code mode variable not found\"\n11: importance_tier: \"normal\"\n12: contextType: \"implementation\"\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Figma CLI Troubleshooting\n16: \n17: > **IMPORTANT:** Examples in this guide are illustrative. The CLI is not assumed to be installed in any given environment, so command output is not reproduced literally — verify the actual surface with `figma-ds-cli --help` (or the relevant subcommand's `--help`) before relying on a flag or verb.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Core Principle\n24: \n25: Find the root cause before applying a fix — symptom fixes create cascading failures. The most common traps are upstream of any Figma operation: the wrong package installed under a colliding name, an old Node, Figma Desktop not open, or a connect mode that was never completed. Work the quick diagnostics first, then jump to the matching symptom row.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: - Diagnose a `figma-ds-cli` install, binary-collision, connect, daemon, or port-conflict failure before mutating anything.\n30: - Resolve an optional Figma MCP (Code Mode) discovery or env-prefix failure.\n31: \n32: ### Key Sources\n33: \n34: - [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - binary identity, connect modes, and the daemon model behind these symptoms.\n35: - [tool_surface.md](tool_surface.md) - the command gating classes the escalation rows reference.\n36: - [mcp_wiring.md](mcp_wiring.md) - the optional Code Mode MCP path and its `.env` prefix.\n37: \n38: Two hard facts shape every fix below:\n39: \n40: - **The canonical binary is `figma-ds-cli`** (silships, npm, MIT). The npm package literally named `figma-cli` is an **unrelated** tool (unic/figma-cli, bin `figma`). The `figma-cli` command only exists when installed from the silships git repo. **Never `npm i -g figma-cli`.**\n41: - **The CLI drives the live Figma Desktop session** — Figma Desktop must be **open with a file**, Node must be **>=18**, and there is **no Figma API key** for the CLI. macOS is the supported baseline; Linux/Windows are experimental and unverified.\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## 2. PREREQUISITES\n46: \n47: Before deeper troubleshooting, confirm the foundation:\n48: \n49: - **5-Check Sequence**: Binary identity -> Node version -> Figma Desktop open -> Connect mode completed -> Daemon health.\n50: - **Platform Awareness**: macOS is the supported baseline. Linux/Windows are experimental and unverified — treat platform-specific failures there as unsupported.\n51: - **Error Capture**: Use `2>&1` so stderr is visible when a command appears to do nothing.\n52: \n53: **Required knowledge**:\n54: \n55: - Basic Bash/terminal usage.\n56: - npm global install and PATH concepts.\n57: - The difference between the safe plugin connect and the gated yolo patch (see `figma_cli_reference.md`).\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n\n(Showing lines 1-60 of 479. Use offset=61 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Figma CLI Troubleshooting\"\ndescription: \"Symptom to cause to fix guide for common figma-ds-cli, daemon, connect, and optional Code Mode MCP issues.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma-cli command not found\"\n  - \"figma-ds-cli troubleshooting\"\n  - \"figma daemon unauthorized\"\n  - \"figma connect safe mode\"\n  - \"figma yolo patch broke\"\n  - \"figma code mode variable not found\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n\n# Figma CLI Troubleshooting\n\n> **IMPORTANT:** Examples in this guide are illustrative. The CLI is not assumed to be installed in any given environment, so command output is not reproduced literally — verify the actual surface with `figma-ds-cli --help` (or the relevant subcommand's `--help`) before relying on a flag or verb.\n\n---\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Figma CLI Troubleshooting\"\ndescription: \"Symptom to cause to fix guide for common figma-ds-cli, daemon, connect, and optional Code Mode MCP issues.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"figma-cli command not found\"\n  - \"figma-ds-cli troubleshooting\"\n  - \"figma daemon unauthorized\"\n  - \"figma connect safe mode\"\n  - \"figma yolo patch broke\"\n  - \"figma code mode variable not found\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n---\n\n# Figma CLI Troubleshooting\n\n> **IMPORTANT:** Examples in this guide are illustrative. The CLI is not assumed to be installed in any given environment, so command output is not reproduced literally — verify the actual surface with `figma-ds-cli --help` (or the relevant subcommand's `--help`) before relying on a flag or verb.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Core Principle\n\nFind the root cause before applying a fix — symptom fixes create cascading failures. The most common traps are upstream of any Figma operation: the wrong package installed under a colliding name, an old Node, Figma Desktop not open, or a connect mode that was never completed. Work the quick diagnostics first, then jump to the matching symptom row.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Diagnose a `figma-ds-cli` install, binary-collision, connect, daemon, or port-conflict failure before mutating anything.\n- Resolve an optional Figma MCP (Code Mode) discovery or env-prefix failure.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n- [figma_cli_reference.md](figma_cli_reference.md) - binary identity, connect modes, and the daemon model behind these symptoms.\n- [tool_surface.md](tool_surface.md) - the command gating classes the escalation rows reference.\n- [mcp_wiring.md](mcp_wiring.md) - the optional Code Mode MCP path and its `.env` prefix.\n\nTwo hard facts shape every fix below:\n\n- **The canonical binary is `figma-ds-cli`** (silships, npm, MIT). The npm package literally named `figma-cli` is an **unrelated** tool (unic/figma-cli, bin `figma`). The `figma-cli` command only exists when installed from the silships git repo. **Never `npm i -g figma-cli`.**\n- **The CLI drives the live Figma Desktop session** — Figma Desktop must be **open with a file**, Node must be **>=18**, and there is **no Figma API key** for the CLI. macOS is the supported baseline; Linux/Windows are experimental and unverified.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PREREQUISITES\n\nBefore deeper troubleshooting, confirm the foundation:\n\n- **5-Check Sequence**: Binary identity -> Node version -> Figma Desktop open -> Connect mode completed -> Daemon health.\n- **Platform Awareness**: macOS is the supported baseline. Linux/Windows are experimental and unverified — treat platform-specific failures there as unsupported.\n- **Error Capture**: Use `2>&1` so stderr is visible when a command appears to do nothing.\n\n**Required knowledge**:\n\n- Basic Bash/terminal usage.\n- npm global install and PATH concepts.\n- The difference between the safe plugin connect and the gated yolo patch (see `figma_cli_reference.md`).\n\n---\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":60,"totalLines":479,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md","time":{"start":1781459296403,"end":1781459296408}},"id":"prt_ec73f9ed6001l0vKtOkmQDQzjG","sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","messageID":"msg_ec73f7f5b001xbG4nRXHMcbwE0"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1781459296723,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","part":{"id":"prt_ec73fa1d2001Z9HW0ci2mnUQTM","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"a927a1bb2656c225c32edb18e83e75f619f01224","messageID":"msg_ec73f7f5b001xbG4nRXHMcbwE0","sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":134818,"input":5767,"output":174,"reasoning":365,"cache":{"write":0,"read":128512}},"cost":0.003443431}}
