{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781459428283,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_Q4taF05e4umWovmbjZ6r8738","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/changelog/v0.1.0.0.md","limit":30},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/changelog/v0.1.0.0.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"mcp-figma v0.1.0.0 - Initial Release\"\n3: ---\n4: \n5: # v0.1.0.0 - Initial Release\n6: \n7: **Released:** 2026-06-14\n8: \n9: Initial (pre-1.0) release of the `mcp-figma` skill. It teaches an agent to drive **Figma Desktop from the terminal** through the silships **figma-cli** (published as `figma-ds-cli`), with an **optional** Figma MCP via this project's Code Mode. The CLI is the primary surface — inspect, export, render, manage tokens/variables/components, and extract/import a design system; the MCP is opt-in and used only to pull Figma design data into the agent for codegen. The spine of the skill is the read-only / mutating / **destructive** gating taxonomy and the `sk-interface-design` handoff that keeps design judgment where it belongs. Modeled on the sibling `mcp-chrome-devtools` (CLI-primary + MCP-via-Code-Mode) and `mcp-open-design` (CLI + optional MCP, daemon model, gated verbs).\n10: \n11: Version is **0.1.0** (pre-1.0) until live external verification (real figma-ds-cli install + connect + MCP discovery) is complete.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## What's New\n16: \n17: ### Core Skill\n18: \n19: - `SKILL.md` — lean house-template runtime instructions\n20:   - Section 1: WHEN TO USE (CLI vs optional-MCP triggers, use cases, anti-patterns)\n21:   - Section 2: SMART ROUTING (direction + binary detection, phase flow, six-intent guarded router)\n22:   - Section 3: HOW IT WORKS (binary verification, Figma Desktop + daemon model, connect modes, command classes, optional Framelink MCP)\n23:   - Section 4: RULES (ALWAYS / NEVER / ESCALATE IF), centered on the `figma-ds-cli` naming trap, safe-default connect, and gating every destructive verb\n24:   - Sections 5-8: references, success criteria, integration points, related resources\n25: \n26: ### References\n27: \n28: - `references/figma_cli_reference.md` — binary identity, connect/daemon model, grouped command examples\n29: - `references/tool_surface.md` — read-only / mutating / destructive / arbitrary taxonomy + the destructive set with rollbacks\n30: - `references/mcp_wiring.md` — the optional Framelink `figma` Code Mode manual, prefixed `.env` token, discover-first flow, `call_tool_chain` example (official Figma Dev Mode MCP noted as out of scope)\n\n(Showing lines 1-30 of 56. Use offset=31 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"mcp-figma v0.1.0.0 - Initial Release\"\n---\n\n# v0.1.0.0 - Initial Release\n\n**Released:** 2026-06-14\n\nInitial (pre-1.0) release of the `mcp-figma` skill. It teaches an agent to drive **Figma Desktop from the terminal** through the silships **figma-cli** (published as `figma-ds-cli`), with an **optional** Figma MCP via this project's Code Mode. The CLI is the primary surface — inspect, export, render, manage tokens/variables/components, and extract/import a design system; the MCP is opt-in and used only to pull Figma design data into the agent for codegen. The spine of the skill is the read-only / mutating / **destructive** gating taxonomy and the `sk-interface-design` handoff that keeps design judgment where it belongs. Modeled on the sibling `mcp-chrome-devtools` (CLI-primary + MCP-via-Code-Mode) and `mcp-open-design` (CLI + optional MCP, daemon model, gated verbs).\n\nVersion is **0.1.0** (pre-1.0) until live external verification (real figma-ds-cli install + connect + MCP discovery) is complete.\n\n---\n\n## What's New\n\n### Core Skill\n\n- `SKILL.md` — lean house-template runtime instructions\n  - Section 1: WHEN TO USE (CLI vs optional-MCP triggers, use cases, anti-patterns)","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/changelog/v0.1.0.0.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"mcp-figma v0.1.0.0 - Initial Release\"\n---\n\n# v0.1.0.0 - Initial Release\n\n**Released:** 2026-06-14\n\nInitial (pre-1.0) release of the `mcp-figma` skill. It teaches an agent to drive **Figma Desktop from the terminal** through the silships **figma-cli** (published as `figma-ds-cli`), with an **optional** Figma MCP via this project's Code Mode. The CLI is the primary surface — inspect, export, render, manage tokens/variables/components, and extract/import a design system; the MCP is opt-in and used only to pull Figma design data into the agent for codegen. The spine of the skill is the read-only / mutating / **destructive** gating taxonomy and the `sk-interface-design` handoff that keeps design judgment where it belongs. Modeled on the sibling `mcp-chrome-devtools` (CLI-primary + MCP-via-Code-Mode) and `mcp-open-design` (CLI + optional MCP, daemon model, gated verbs).\n\nVersion is **0.1.0** (pre-1.0) until live external verification (real figma-ds-cli install + connect + MCP discovery) is complete.\n\n---\n\n## What's New\n\n### Core Skill\n\n- `SKILL.md` — lean house-template runtime instructions\n  - Section 1: WHEN TO USE (CLI vs optional-MCP triggers, use cases, anti-patterns)\n  - Section 2: SMART ROUTING (direction + binary detection, phase flow, six-intent guarded router)\n  - Section 3: HOW IT WORKS (binary verification, Figma Desktop + daemon model, connect modes, command classes, optional Framelink MCP)\n  - Section 4: RULES (ALWAYS / NEVER / ESCALATE IF), centered on the `figma-ds-cli` naming trap, safe-default connect, and gating every destructive verb\n  - Sections 5-8: references, success criteria, integration points, related resources\n\n### References\n\n- `references/figma_cli_reference.md` — binary identity, connect/daemon model, grouped command examples\n- `references/tool_surface.md` — read-only / mutating / destructive / arbitrary taxonomy + the destructive set with rollbacks\n- `references/mcp_wiring.md` — the optional Framelink `figma` Code Mode manual, prefixed `.env` token, discover-first flow, `call_tool_chain` example (official Figma Dev Mode MCP noted as out of scope)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":30,"totalLines":56,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/changelog/v0.1.0.0.md","time":{"start":1781459428277,"end":1781459428282}},"id":"prt_ec741a1d6001Itqt8hGoS97Oeb","sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","messageID":"msg_ec74194ce001zye4E5KKoDdsaX"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781459428761,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_CHsjxD3DFZkWauwZG73f0632","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/INSTALL_GUIDE.md","limit":40},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/INSTALL_GUIDE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # mcp-figma Installation Guide\n2: \n3: Complete installation and configuration guide for the `mcp-figma` skill, which drives Figma Desktop from the terminal through the silships CLI. Installs and verifies the silships **`figma-ds-cli`** binary (the primary tool), sets up the safe-default plugin connection and local daemon, and optionally wires the community Framelink Figma MCP through this project's Code Mode for pulling design context the other way. The CLI works fully on its own and the MCP is opt-in. No Figma API key is needed for the CLI.\n4: \n5: > **Naming trap, read first.** Install **`figma-ds-cli`**, the unambiguous npm package for the silships tool. The npm package literally named **`figma-cli` is an UNRELATED tool** (unic/figma-cli, by Fredi Bach, which installs a bin named `figma`). **Never run `npm i -g figma-cli`.** A `figma-cli` command exists as a second name for the silships tool only when you build from the silships repo.\n6: > **Package:** `figma-ds-cli` (silships) | **Dependencies:** Node.js 18+, Figma Desktop, macOS baseline\n7: \n8: **Version:** 0.1.0 | **Updated:** 2026-06-14 | **Transport:** local daemon (HTTP 127.0.0.1:3456)\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## 0. AI-FIRST INSTALL GUIDE\n13: \n14: **Copy and paste this prompt to your AI assistant to get installation help:**\n15: \n16: ```\n17: I want to set up the mcp-figma skill (the silships figma-ds-cli, plus the optional Code Mode Figma MCP).\n18: \n19: Please help me:\n20: 1. Check that I have Node.js 18+ and npm installed\n21: 2. Run the skill's scripts/install.sh, which installs figma-ds-cli and auto-upgrades the stale npm 1.0.0 to the full repo 1.2.0\n22: 3. Verify the binary identity with scripts/doctor.sh (confirm figma-ds-cli resolved, not the unrelated unic figma-cli)\n23: 4. Open Figma Desktop with a file, then connect with the safe default (connect-safe.sh)\n24: 5. (Optional) Wire the Code Mode Framelink figma manual by adding figma_FIGMA_API_KEY to .env\n25: \n26: My platform is: [macOS / Linux / Windows]\n27: \n28: Guide me through each step with the exact commands needed. Never run `npm i -g figma-cli`.\n29: ```\n30: \n31: The AI will:\n32: - Verify Node.js 18 or newer is available on your system\n33: - Run `scripts/install.sh`, which installs and verifies only and never connects or patches Figma\n34: - Confirm `figma-ds-cli --version` is at least 1.2.0 and that the unrelated `figma-cli` is not the resolved binary\n35: - Walk you through the safe-default plugin connection and a daemon health check\n36: - Wire the optional Code Mode Figma MCP only if you ask for it\n37: \n38: **Expected setup time:** 3 to 8 minutes\n39: \n40: ### Quick Success Check (30 seconds)\n\n(Showing lines 1-40 of 461. Use offset=41 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# mcp-figma Installation Guide\n\nComplete installation and configuration guide for the `mcp-figma` skill, which drives Figma Desktop from the terminal through the silships CLI. Installs and verifies the silships **`figma-ds-cli`** binary (the primary tool), sets up the safe-default plugin connection and local daemon, and optionally wires the community Framelink Figma MCP through this project's Code Mode for pulling design context the other way. The CLI works fully on its own and the MCP is opt-in. No Figma API key is needed for the CLI.\n\n> **Naming trap, read first.** Install **`figma-ds-cli`**, the unambiguous npm package for the silships tool. The npm package literally named **`figma-cli` is an UNRELATED tool** (unic/figma-cli, by Fredi Bach, which installs a bin named `figma`). **Never run `npm i -g figma-cli`.** A `figma-cli` command exists as a second name for the silships tool only when you build from the silships repo.\n> **Package:** `figma-ds-cli` (silships) | **Dependencies:** Node.js 18+, Figma Desktop, macOS baseline\n\n**Version:** 0.1.0 | **Updated:** 2026-06-14 | **Transport:** local daemon (HTTP 127.0.0.1:3456)\n\n---\n\n## 0. AI-FIRST INSTALL GUIDE\n\n**Copy and paste this prompt to your AI assistant to get installation help:**\n\n```\nI want to set up the mcp-figma skill (the silships figma-ds-cli, plus the optional Code Mode Figma MCP).\n\nPlease help me:\n1. Check that I have Node.js 18+ and npm installed","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/INSTALL_GUIDE.md","text":"# mcp-figma Installation Guide\n\nComplete installation and configuration guide for the `mcp-figma` skill, which drives Figma Desktop from the terminal through the silships CLI. Installs and verifies the silships **`figma-ds-cli`** binary (the primary tool), sets up the safe-default plugin connection and local daemon, and optionally wires the community Framelink Figma MCP through this project's Code Mode for pulling design context the other way. The CLI works fully on its own and the MCP is opt-in. No Figma API key is needed for the CLI.\n\n> **Naming trap, read first.** Install **`figma-ds-cli`**, the unambiguous npm package for the silships tool. The npm package literally named **`figma-cli` is an UNRELATED tool** (unic/figma-cli, by Fredi Bach, which installs a bin named `figma`). **Never run `npm i -g figma-cli`.** A `figma-cli` command exists as a second name for the silships tool only when you build from the silships repo.\n> **Package:** `figma-ds-cli` (silships) | **Dependencies:** Node.js 18+, Figma Desktop, macOS baseline\n\n**Version:** 0.1.0 | **Updated:** 2026-06-14 | **Transport:** local daemon (HTTP 127.0.0.1:3456)\n\n---\n\n## 0. AI-FIRST INSTALL GUIDE\n\n**Copy and paste this prompt to your AI assistant to get installation help:**\n\n```\nI want to set up the mcp-figma skill (the silships figma-ds-cli, plus the optional Code Mode Figma MCP).\n\nPlease help me:\n1. Check that I have Node.js 18+ and npm installed\n2. Run the skill's scripts/install.sh, which installs figma-ds-cli and auto-upgrades the stale npm 1.0.0 to the full repo 1.2.0\n3. Verify the binary identity with scripts/doctor.sh (confirm figma-ds-cli resolved, not the unrelated unic figma-cli)\n4. Open Figma Desktop with a file, then connect with the safe default (connect-safe.sh)\n5. (Optional) Wire the Code Mode Framelink figma manual by adding figma_FIGMA_API_KEY to .env\n\nMy platform is: [macOS / Linux / Windows]\n\nGuide me through each step with the exact commands needed. Never run `npm i -g figma-cli`.\n```\n\nThe AI will:\n- Verify Node.js 18 or newer is available on your system\n- Run `scripts/install.sh`, which installs and verifies only and never connects or patches Figma\n- Confirm `figma-ds-cli --version` is at least 1.2.0 and that the unrelated `figma-cli` is not the resolved binary\n- Walk you through the safe-default plugin connection and a daemon health check\n- Wire the optional Code Mode Figma MCP only if you ask for it\n\n**Expected setup time:** 3 to 8 minutes\n\n### Quick Success Check (30 seconds)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":40,"totalLines":461,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/INSTALL_GUIDE.md","time":{"start":1781459428757,"end":1781459428761}},"id":"prt_ec741a3f70019zYVj3vfr0wuUa","sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","messageID":"msg_ec74194ce001zye4E5KKoDdsaX"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781459429101,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_aulnu90831SR4lL4x9Q19279","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/graph-metadata.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/graph-metadata.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"schema_version\": 2,\n3:   \"skill_id\": \"mcp-figma\",\n4:   \"family\": \"mcp\",\n5:   \"category\": \"mcp-tool\",\n6:   \"edges\": {\n7:     \"depends_on\": [\n8:       {\n9:         \"target\": \"sk-interface-design\",\n10:         \"weight\": 0.7,\n11:         \"context\": \"When a Figma read or export feeds a design decision, apply sk-interface-design's anti-default judgment before deciding\"\n12:       },\n13:       {\n14:         \"target\": \"mcp-code-mode\",\n15:         \"weight\": 0.45,\n16:         \"context\": \"The optional Figma MCP (Framelink figma manual) is invoked through Code Mode when MCP context is needed\"\n17:       }\n18:     ],\n19:     \"enhances\": [\n20:       {\n21:         \"target\": \"sk-code\",\n22:         \"weight\": 0.4,\n23:         \"context\": \"Figma exports, DESIGN.md, variables, and screenshots feed application implementation that sk-code governs and verifies\"\n24:       }\n25:     ],\n26:     \"siblings\": [\n27:       {\n28:         \"target\": \"mcp-open-design\",\n29:         \"weight\": 0.55,\n30:         \"context\": \"Sibling terminal-driven design tool with a daemon model, gated mutating verbs, and an sk-interface-design handoff\"\n31:       },\n32:       {\n33:         \"target\": \"mcp-chrome-devtools\",\n34:         \"weight\": 0.5,\n35:         \"context\": \"Sibling CLI-primary plus MCP-via-Code-Mode skill sharing the same router and gating pattern\"\n36:       }\n37:     ],\n38:     \"conflicts_with\": [],\n39:     \"prerequisite_for\": []\n40:   },\n41:   \"manual\": {\n42:     \"depends_on\": [],\n43:     \"related_to\": [\"sk-interface-design\", \"sk-code\", \"mcp-code-mode\", \"mcp-open-design\", \"mcp-chrome-devtools\"]\n44:   },\n45:   \"domains\": [\"figma\", \"design-to-code\", \"design-systems\", \"cli\", \"mcp\", \"figma-desktop\"],\n46:   \"intent_signals\": [\n47:     \"figma cli\",\n48:     \"figma-ds-cli\",\n49:     \"figma desktop\",\n50:     \"render in figma\",\n51:     \"figma tokens\",\n52:     \"figma variables\",\n53:     \"extract DESIGN.md\",\n54:     \"export from figma\",\n55:     \"connect to figma\",\n56:     \"figma daemon\",\n57:     \"figma mcp\"\n58:   ],\n59:   \"derived\": {\n60:     \"trigger_phrases\": [\n61:       \"figma cli\",\n62:       \"figma-ds-cli\",\n63:       \"figma desktop\",\n64:       \"render in figma\",\n65:       \"figma tokens\",\n66:       \"extract design.md\",\n67:       \"connect to figma\",\n68:       \"figma mcp\"\n69:     ],\n70:     \"key_topics\": [\n71:       \"figma-ds-cli binary (and the unrelated figma-cli npm collision)\",\n72:       \"Figma Desktop session + local daemon (HTTP 127.0.0.1:3456)\",\n73:       \"safe (plugin) vs yolo (app.asar patch) connect modes\",\n74:       \"read-only / mutating / destructive command gating\",\n75:       \"design-system extract (DESIGN.md) and import (tailwind/css/tokens/storybook)\",\n76:       \"tokens, variables, var:name binding\",\n77:       \"optional Framelink figma MCP via Code Mode\",\n78:       \"sk-interface-design handoff for design judgment\"\n79:     ],\n80:     \"intent_signals\": [\n81:       \"figma\",\n82:       \"figma-ds-cli\",\n83:       \"figma desktop\",\n84:       \"design tokens\",\n85:       \"figma export\",\n86:       \"figma mcp\",\n87:       \"code mode figma\"\n88:     ],\n89:     \"key_files\": [\n90:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/SKILL.md\",\n91:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/README.md\",\n92:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/INSTALL_GUIDE.md\",\n93:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/figma_cli_reference.md\",\n94:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/tool_surface.md\",\n95:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md\",\n96:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md\",\n97:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md\",\n98:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\",\n99:       \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/changelog/v0.1.0.0.md\"\n100:     ],\n101:     \"entities\": [\n102:       {\"name\": \"mcp-figma\", \"kind\": \"skill\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/SKILL.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n103:       {\"name\": \"README\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/README.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n104:       {\"name\": \"figma_cli_reference\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/figma_cli_reference.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n105:       {\"name\": \"tool_surface\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/tool_surface.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n106:       {\"name\": \"mcp_wiring\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n107:       {\"name\": \"troubleshooting\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"}\n108:     ],\n109:     \"causal_summary\": \"mcp-figma teaches a terminal agent to drive Figma Desktop through the silships figma-cli, published to npm as figma-ds-cli (the npm package literally named figma-cli is an unrelated tool by unic, bin 'figma' - never install it). figma-cli has no MCP of its own; it drives the live Figma Desktop session via a local daemon (HTTP 127.0.0.1:3456, X-Daemon-Token). Connect is either safe (FigCli plugin, no patch - the default) or yolo (patches Figma app.asar, CDP 9222 - gated, rollback via unpatch). The CLI is primary for authoring/modifying/exporting in Figma; an optional Figma MCP (the community Framelink figma manual already in this repo's Code Mode) is opt-in for pulling design data into the agent for codegen. Commands are gated read-only / mutating / destructive, with eval/raw/run treated as arbitrary mutation and local exports requiring explicit no-overwrite paths. Pairs with sk-interface-design (design judgment) and sk-code (adapting exports into an app). Modeled on mcp-chrome-devtools and mcp-open-design.\",\n110:     \"source_docs\": [\n111:       \"SKILL.md\",\n112:       \"README.md\",\n113:       \"INSTALL_GUIDE.md\",\n114:       \"references/figma_cli_reference.md\",\n115:       \"references/tool_surface.md\",\n116:       \"references/mcp_wiring.md\",\n117:       \"references/troubleshooting.md\",\n118:       \"feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md\",\n119:       \"manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\",\n120:       \"changelog/v0.1.0.0.md\"\n121:     ],\n122:     \"created_at\": \"2026-06-14T16:00:00Z\",\n123:     \"last_updated_at\": \"2026-06-14T16:00:00Z\"\n124:   }\n125: }\n\n(End of file - total 125 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"schema_version\": 2,\n  \"skill_id\": \"mcp-figma\",\n  \"family\": \"mcp\",\n  \"category\": \"mcp-tool\",\n  \"edges\": {\n    \"depends_on\": [\n      {\n        \"target\": \"sk-interface-design\",\n        \"weight\": 0.7,\n        \"context\": \"When a Figma read or export feeds a design decision, apply sk-interface-design's anti-default judgment before deciding\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"target\": \"mcp-code-mode\",\n        \"weight\": 0.45,\n        \"context\": \"The optional Figma MCP (Framelink figma manual) is invoked through Code Mode when MCP context is needed\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"enhances\": [\n      {","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/graph-metadata.json","text":"{\n  \"schema_version\": 2,\n  \"skill_id\": \"mcp-figma\",\n  \"family\": \"mcp\",\n  \"category\": \"mcp-tool\",\n  \"edges\": {\n    \"depends_on\": [\n      {\n        \"target\": \"sk-interface-design\",\n        \"weight\": 0.7,\n        \"context\": \"When a Figma read or export feeds a design decision, apply sk-interface-design's anti-default judgment before deciding\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"target\": \"mcp-code-mode\",\n        \"weight\": 0.45,\n        \"context\": \"The optional Figma MCP (Framelink figma manual) is invoked through Code Mode when MCP context is needed\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"enhances\": [\n      {\n        \"target\": \"sk-code\",\n        \"weight\": 0.4,\n        \"context\": \"Figma exports, DESIGN.md, variables, and screenshots feed application implementation that sk-code governs and verifies\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"siblings\": [\n      {\n        \"target\": \"mcp-open-design\",\n        \"weight\": 0.55,\n        \"context\": \"Sibling terminal-driven design tool with a daemon model, gated mutating verbs, and an sk-interface-design handoff\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"target\": \"mcp-chrome-devtools\",\n        \"weight\": 0.5,\n        \"context\": \"Sibling CLI-primary plus MCP-via-Code-Mode skill sharing the same router and gating pattern\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"conflicts_with\": [],\n    \"prerequisite_for\": []\n  },\n  \"manual\": {\n    \"depends_on\": [],\n    \"related_to\": [\"sk-interface-design\", \"sk-code\", \"mcp-code-mode\", \"mcp-open-design\", \"mcp-chrome-devtools\"]\n  },\n  \"domains\": [\"figma\", \"design-to-code\", \"design-systems\", \"cli\", \"mcp\", \"figma-desktop\"],\n  \"intent_signals\": [\n    \"figma cli\",\n    \"figma-ds-cli\",\n    \"figma desktop\",\n    \"render in figma\",\n    \"figma tokens\",\n    \"figma variables\",\n    \"extract DESIGN.md\",\n    \"export from figma\",\n    \"connect to figma\",\n    \"figma daemon\",\n    \"figma mcp\"\n  ],\n  \"derived\": {\n    \"trigger_phrases\": [\n      \"figma cli\",\n      \"figma-ds-cli\",\n      \"figma desktop\",\n      \"render in figma\",\n      \"figma tokens\",\n      \"extract design.md\",\n      \"connect to figma\",\n      \"figma mcp\"\n    ],\n    \"key_topics\": [\n      \"figma-ds-cli binary (and the unrelated figma-cli npm collision)\",\n      \"Figma Desktop session + local daemon (HTTP 127.0.0.1:3456)\",\n      \"safe (plugin) vs yolo (app.asar patch) connect modes\",\n      \"read-only / mutating / destructive command gating\",\n      \"design-system extract (DESIGN.md) and import (tailwind/css/tokens/storybook)\",\n      \"tokens, variables, var:name binding\",\n      \"optional Framelink figma MCP via Code Mode\",\n      \"sk-interface-design handoff for design judgment\"\n    ],\n    \"intent_signals\": [\n      \"figma\",\n      \"figma-ds-cli\",\n      \"figma desktop\",\n      \"design tokens\",\n      \"figma export\",\n      \"figma mcp\",\n      \"code mode figma\"\n    ],\n    \"key_files\": [\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/SKILL.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/README.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/INSTALL_GUIDE.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/figma_cli_reference.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/tool_surface.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\",\n      \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/changelog/v0.1.0.0.md\"\n    ],\n    \"entities\": [\n      {\"name\": \"mcp-figma\", \"kind\": \"skill\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/SKILL.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n      {\"name\": \"README\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/README.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n      {\"name\": \"figma_cli_reference\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/figma_cli_reference.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n      {\"name\": \"tool_surface\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/tool_surface.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n      {\"name\": \"mcp_wiring\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/mcp_wiring.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"},\n      {\"name\": \"troubleshooting\", \"kind\": \"reference\", \"path\": \".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/references/troubleshooting.md\", \"source\": \"derived\"}\n    ],\n    \"causal_summary\": \"mcp-figma teaches a terminal agent to drive Figma Desktop through the silships figma-cli, published to npm as figma-ds-cli (the npm package literally named figma-cli is an unrelated tool by unic, bin 'figma' - never install it). figma-cli has no MCP of its own; it drives the live Figma Desktop session via a local daemon (HTTP 127.0.0.1:3456, X-Daemon-Token). Connect is either safe (FigCli plugin, no patch - the default) or yolo (patches Figma app.asar, CDP 9222 - gated, rollback via unpatch). The CLI is primary for authoring/modifying/exporting in Figma; an optional Figma MCP (the community Framelink figma manual already in this repo's Code Mode) is opt-in for pulling design data into the agent for codegen. Commands are gated read-only / mutating / destructive, with eval/raw/run treated as arbitrary mutation and local exports requiring explicit no-overwrite paths. Pairs with sk-interface-design (design judgment) and sk-code (adapting exports into an app). Modeled on mcp-chrome-devtools and mcp-open-design.\",\n    \"source_docs\": [\n      \"SKILL.md\",\n      \"README.md\",\n      \"INSTALL_GUIDE.md\",\n      \"references/figma_cli_reference.md\",\n      \"references/tool_surface.md\",\n      \"references/mcp_wiring.md\",\n      \"references/troubleshooting.md\",\n      \"feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md\",\n      \"manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md\",\n      \"changelog/v0.1.0.0.md\"\n    ],\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-06-14T16:00:00Z\",\n    \"last_updated_at\": \"2026-06-14T16:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":125,"totalLines":125,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/mcp-figma/graph-metadata.json","time":{"start":1781459429096,"end":1781459429100}},"id":"prt_ec741a5b80019kskm2o5Asf68M","sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","messageID":"msg_ec74194ce001zye4E5KKoDdsaX"}}
