{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781459660478,"sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_Q7Yp8IAdJI3mZzZBho2i2647","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support/review/session-audit/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro/deep-review-strategy.md","limit":20,"offset":1},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support/review/session-audit/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro/deep-review-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking\n2: \n3: ## Topic\n4: Review of the mcp-figma skill package and phase-parent spec folder (`151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support`). The skill drives Figma Desktop from the terminal via figma-ds-cli with an optional Figma MCP path through Code Mode. Both child phases (001 research, 002 build) are marked Complete. Review target is the shipped skill at `.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/` plus the phase spec documents.\n5: \n6: ## Review Dimensions (remaining)\n7: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n8: - [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n9: - [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n10: - [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n11: - [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n12: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n13: \n14: ## Non-Goals\n15: - Not reviewing the upstream silships/figma-cli repo or the Figma Desktop app itself (third-party, read-only input)\n16: - Not reviewing the npm `figma-cli` package (unrelated, named only as a trap)\n17: - Not evaluating design taste or interface aesthetics (owned by sk-interface-design)\n18: \n19: ## Stop Conditions\n20: - Max 10 iterations reached\n\n(Showing lines 1-20 of 116. Use offset=21 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking\n\n## Topic\nReview of the mcp-figma skill package and phase-parent spec folder (`151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support`). The skill drives Figma Desktop from the terminal via figma-ds-cli with an optional Figma MCP path through Code Mode. Both child phases (001 research, 002 build) are marked Complete. Review target is the shipped skill at `.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/` plus the phase spec documents.\n\n## Review Dimensions (remaining)\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n- [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n- [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n- [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## Non-Goals\n- Not reviewing the upstream silships/figma-cli repo or the Figma Desktop app itself (third-party, read-only input)\n- Not reviewing the npm `figma-cli` package (unrelated, named only as a trap)\n- Not evaluating design taste or interface aesthetics (owned by sk-interface-design)\n\n## Stop Conditions\n- Max 10 iterations reached","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support/review/session-audit/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro/deep-review-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking\n\n## Topic\nReview of the mcp-figma skill package and phase-parent spec folder (`151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support`). The skill drives Figma Desktop from the terminal via figma-ds-cli with an optional Figma MCP path through Code Mode. Both child phases (001 research, 002 build) are marked Complete. Review target is the shipped skill at `.opencode/skills/mcp-figma/` plus the phase spec documents.\n\n## Review Dimensions (remaining)\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n- [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n- [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n- [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## Non-Goals\n- Not reviewing the upstream silships/figma-cli repo or the Figma Desktop app itself (third-party, read-only input)\n- Not reviewing the npm `figma-cli` package (unrelated, named only as a trap)\n- Not evaluating design taste or interface aesthetics (owned by sk-interface-design)\n\n## Stop Conditions\n- Max 10 iterations reached","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":20,"totalLines":116,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/151-mcp-figma-with-direct-cli-support/review/session-audit/lineages/deepseek-v4-pro/deep-review-strategy.md","time":{"start":1781459660465,"end":1781459660477}},"id":"prt_ec7452bde0012BnrWYN1l3HQ6t","sessionID":"ses_138c2bafbfferH0GdGNnzVMgNJ","messageID":"msg_ec7451fa60014azK79RqanjsXm"}}
